	<!-- Main Post Body -->
	<table width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<td bgcolor="#4D4D73"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"></td><td width="100%" bgcolor="#4D4D73"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
	Posted 02-05-2004 <font color="#FEDE01">08:37 PM</font></font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">As many of you know we've been struggling to keep our head above water so we can continue being a good resource for clerics and for EverQuest players in the future. We have many great ideas and working on many great resources that will make this website very strong and powerful, both as a community and as a source of quality information.<br />
<br />
Because of the fluxuation in user support through donations and a much lower purchase level in our store from what we expected, we're entertaining the idea of offering more features/content/tools to people paying a monthly fee, as a membership service.<br />
<br />
But before we even go down that path I'm surveying you guys first. We're not blind here, nor do we ignore your ideas. Quite the contrary. Everything you see on this site now ranging from colors to forum/site features and our Roadmap is strongly and always based on user feedback.<br />
<br />
This is a site for you and a tool for you to enjoy whenever you want to. It's not free though, and every month we grow a little more, and every month it requires lots more resources on the server side to keep the site up and working at a decent level.<br />
<br />
<b>So, here's the question: Would you be willing to pay?<br />
<br />
How much is a decent monthly amount to pay for premium services? What should this include. What are you wanting in return for your support?</b><br />
<br />
These are the burning questions we need answered, and I'm looking forward to reading what you have to say about it.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">
<img src="signature.php?userid=1&dateline=1056943942" border="0" alt=""><br>

</font></p></p>
	<p></p>
