	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">The more I think about it, the more I realize just how much I've come to love and depend on this site.<br />
<br />
In general principle, I hate sites that begin to charge monthly fees for access.  I suppose I've become accustomed to the concept that the Internet is (and should be) free - nevermind the reality that it's... well, not.<br />
<br />
I definitely appreciate your taking the time to talk to us, and to get our opinions and thoughts rather than simply launching on a 'you're going to have to give us this, this, and this, or else you can't see our super-duper-cool part of the site' campaign.<br />
<br />
I answered 'No, I can't afford it' to the poll, but I think in reality it depends largely on the asking price.  If it really is $5 or possibly even $10 per year, then I suppose I can manage.  (After all, I pay much more than that to play EQ itself, right?)  If it's more on the order of $5 per month, then I may have to go shopping for a new site.  I'm in college, and my cash flow is...  well, not that stable.  I buy things by the semester or year, never by the month, and while $5 a month still isn't much...  with no job, I'm not sure how I'm going to pay for EQ at all once my current year's subscription runs out.  I have $3.55 in my bank account.  And the balance isn't changing...  <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue">  (Luckily my meals are paid for, or I'd be in trouble...)<br />
<br />
I guess...  well, I don't have much of a point here (<img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue">), except to say thank you for stopping to listen to us, and thank you for putting this wonderful site together.  As much as I have come to hate the concept of subscription websites (The Sims Resource comes to mind (yes, I'm a Sims junkie as well as an EverCrack user)), I think I would understand and in this particular case, probably even stick around.  The more time I spend browsing The Safehouse, the more I love it here.  <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="Smile"></font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">

- Commence -<BR>52 Cleric of Tunare<BR>Commence@eqcleric.com
</font></p></p>
	<p></p>
	</td></tr></table>
