	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">I think something that could make donations come in more readily is something like the feature on EZBoard, where it shows how much has been donated and how much is needed.  Giving people a goal that they can attain is always more motivating than everything going into a "black box", so to speak.<br />
<br />
I enjoy this site, but I got caught in the "I don't really have enough money this month, but next paycheck I'll donate" cycle.  The past two years haven't been good for my boyfriend and I jobwise between layoffs and contract work.  However, if I'd known that x amount of money was needed per month for this site I would have made more of an effort to donate something.<br />
<br />
In that regard paying monthly for the site wouldn't bother me.  I believe in it enough to support it.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
